    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-17T04:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-17T04:30:00-05:00" n="68"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/921: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Batavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dickover</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Batavia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-17T17:00:00+07:30"
                            >July 17, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 17—10:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have discussed the fall of the Cabinet<note n="90" xml:id="d68fn90">For
                        resignation of Admiral Yonai’s Cabinet on July 16, see telegram No. 590,
                        July 17, 5 p.m., from the Ambassador in Japan, <ref target="#pg_964">p.
                            964</ref>.</note> and the rise of a presumably fascist party in Japan
                    with several government officials including the Governor General and the
                    Admiral. They all are decidedly apprehensive of future developments in the Far
                    East, [as] Germany, Japan may be preparing to seize this “golden opportunity” to
                    eliminate Western influence and to establish its “new order” in this part of the
                    world. They all desired to know what the United States would do in <pb
                        facs="0060" n="52" xml:id="pg_52"/> such case, to which I replied that it
                    depends on the will of the people as expressed through Congress. I received the
                    impression that the Netherlands Indies in this period of crisis is more and more
                    hoping for some indication that it will be protected by the American fleet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dickover</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
